{% comment %}
  Emit a root-relative base path so asset/nav links resolve against the
  current host. This avoids Jekyll serve's `-H 0.0.0.0` writing absolute
  http://0.0.0.0:4000/... URLs that the browser cannot load (CSS/JS/images
  would 502 and the page would render unstyled). Relative links work in both
  local Docker preview and GitHub Pages (root deployment).
{% endcomment %}
{% assign base_path = site.baseurl %}

